SIMPLE: needs
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Needs
<hw>Needs</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[Orig. gen. of
<ets>need</ets>, used as an adverb. Cf. <er>-wards</er>.]</ety> <def>Of
necessity; necessarily; indispensably; -- often with <xex>must</xex>,
and equivalent to <xex>of need</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A man must <qex>needs</qex> love mauger his head.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And he must <qex>needs</qex> go through Samaria.</q> <rj><qau>John
iv. 4.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He would <qex>needs</qex> know the cause of his repulse.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir J. Davies.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Needscost</ent>⟦br⟧
